}}'''Ooty''' {{audio|Ooty.ogg|pronunciation}}, short for '''Ootacamund''' {{audio|Ootacamund.ogg|pronunciation}} (officially, '''Udhagamandalam''' ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: உதகமண்டலம்) sometimes abbreviated to '''Udhagai''' Tamil: உதகை), is a town, a [[municipality]] and the district capital of [[the Nilgiris district]] in the [[South India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Tamil Nadu]]. 

Ootacamund is a popular [[hill station]] located in the [[Nilgiri Hills]]. Udhagamandalam is the older and official Tamil name for the town. Ooty stands at an approximate height of 9,080 feet (2,767 m) above sea level.

